<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFFFFBEFC959F5C6C767E93" pageId="18" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFFFFBEFC959F5C6A607E10" blockId="18.[831,1437,792,1011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFFFFBEFC959F5C6ABD7E51" bold="true" box="[831,944,792,816]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">Remarks:</emphasis>
It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFFFFBEFBC79F5D6C007E51" box="[1133,1293,792,816]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Frondicularia" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="18" pageNumber="32" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="archiaciana">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFFFFBEFBC79F5D6C007E51" box="[1133,1293,792,816]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">F. archiaciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a terminal spine and the greatest breadth toward the initial end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFFFFBEFC959F3D6C767E93" blockId="18.[831,1437,792,1011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFFFFBEFC959F3D6D707EF0" bold="true" box="[831,1149,889,913]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Maastrichtian by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956) and in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene by LUGER (1985). It is recorded in the Maastrichtian of Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
